## 3. Modelos de Datos (Prisma)

### 3.1 Nuevos modelos a agregar al [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO%20CORP/Proyecto%20Pachanga/backend/prisma/schema.prisma)

```prisma
enum CustomerSource {
  QR_SCAN       // Escaneó QR en el bar
  RESERVATION   // Hizo reserva online
  MANUAL        // Admin lo registró manual
}

enum MessageStatus {
  QUEUED
  SENT
  DELIVERED
  READ
  FAILED
}

enum MessageType {
  WELCOME
  BIRTHDAY
  PROMO
  REACTIVATION
}

model Customer {
  id            String          @id @default(uuid())
  name          String
  phone         String          @unique  // +573219992719 (E.164 format)
  birthDate     DateTime?       @map("birth_date") @db.Date
  rating        Int?            // 1-5 estrellas del servicio
  source        CustomerSource  @default(QR_SCAN)
  totalVisits   Int             @default(1) @map("total_visits")
  lastVisitAt   DateTime        @default(now()) @map("last_visit_at")
  optIn         Boolean         @default(true) @map("opt_in")
  notes         String?
  isActive      Boolean         @default(true) @map("is_active")
  createdAt     DateTime        @default(now()) @map("created_at")
  updatedAt     DateTime        @updatedAt @map("updated_at")

  messages      WhatsAppMessage[]
  interactions  Interaction[]

  @@index([phone])
  @@index([birthDate])
  @@index([lastVisitAt])
  @@map("customers")
}

model Interaction {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  customerId  String   @map("customer_id")
  customer    Customer @relation(fields: [customerId], references: [id])
  type        String   // "visit", "qr_scan", "reservation", "birthday_redeemed"
  metadata    Json?    // { tableId, formData, etc. }
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")

  @@index([customerId])
  @@index([createdAt])
  @@map("interactions")
}

model WhatsAppMessage {
  id          String        @id @default(uuid())
  customerId  String        @map("customer_id")
  customer    Customer      @relation(fields: [customerId], references: [id])
  type        MessageType
  templateName String       @map("template_name")
  status      MessageStatus @default(QUEUED)
  waMessageId String?       @map("wa_message_id") // ID devuelto por Meta
  sentAt      DateTime?     @map("sent_at")
  deliveredAt DateTime?     @map("delivered_at")
  readAt      DateTime?     @map("read_at")
  errorCode   String?       @map("error_code")
  createdAt   DateTime      @default(now()) @map("created_at")

  @@index([customerId])
  @@index([type, status])
  @@index([sentAt])
  @@map("whatsapp_messages")
}

model CrmConfig {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  key       String   @unique  // "birthday_min_group", "welcome_template", etc.
  value     String
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at")

  @@map("crm_config")
}
```

### 3.2 Relación con modelos existentes

| Modelo existente | Relación | Notas |
|---|---|---|
| `Reservation.customerPhone` | → `Customer.phone` | Se puede vincular automáticamente al crear reserva |
| [User](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO%20CORP/Proyecto%20Pachanga/backend/src/types/express.d.ts#5-11) (admin) | opera el dashboard CRM | Sin relación directa, usa JWT existente |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> No se agrega FK directa de [Reservation](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO%20CORP/Proyecto%20Pachanga/app/src/types/reservation.types.ts#5-19) → `Customer` para mantener backward compatibility. La vinculación es lógica por `phone`.

